        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 14 at 1:15PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 114 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms over
western and northern Person County, the strongest near Alton, or 7
miles northwest of Roxboro, moving north at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Roxboro, Concord, Bethel Hill, Bushy Fork, Hyco Lake, Moriah, Mayo
Reservoir, Hyco Marina, and Surl.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
